$ Stellarium API: core.setSelectedObjectInfo

`core.setSelectedObjectInfo(level)` allows to set the amount of information that is shown when an object is selected (see
→ Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/selectObjectByName[`core.selectObjectByName()`]).

code {
core.setSelectedObjectInfo('AllInfo');
core.setSelectedObjectInfo('ShortInfo');
core.setSelectedObjectInfo('None');
code }

sa:
  The GUI dialog → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/GUI/popups/Configuration/Information[Configuration -> Information] allows to choose the amount of information with much more details.
